sequenceDiagram
    participant IPS as IPS (SFTP)
    participant S3 as S3 bucket
    participant MW as ETL Middleware
    participant Import as Spryker DataImport
    participant DB as Spryker DB
    participant MQ as RabbitMQ (multi-queue)
    participant Redis as Redis (P&S)

    IPS->>S3: Deliver FULL XML (~1.5M productdata tags)
    Note over S3: Spryker is NOT a file proxy
    MW->>S3: Fetch large XML
    MW->>MW: Split into per-entity/per-store chunks
    MW->>Import: Hand chunks
    Import->>DB: CTE / PDO bulk write (no per-row ORM)
    Import->>DB: Record import run (type, started, finished, success)
    DB->>MQ: Emit events
    par Multiple publisher queues
        MQ->>Redis: Publish & Sync (tuned chunk size)
    end
    Note over Redis: Only Storefront-relevant product data exported
    Note over Import,Redis: Budget ~30 min (not strict), scaling toward 26 mio parts
